    "body": "Closing this for now, as it hasn't come up again, and naive attempts at detecting SSSE3 support at compile time do not work. One issue is that `rustc` doesn't consider the `ssse3` feature enabled unless it is explicitly turned on (e.g. via `-C target-cpu=native`), so this test fails even on modern CPUs:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n// BLST requires SSSE3 on x86_64.\r\n#[cfg(all(feature = \"supranational\", target_arch = \"x86_64\"))]\r\nstatic_assertions::assert_cfg!(target_feature = \"ssse3\", \"BLST requires SSSE3\");\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt's \"future work\" to try `target-cpu=native` builds to see if they are appreciably faster.",
